Process Data

# read length of days
N_days = length(strsplit(inp[2],"\\s+",perl = TRUE)[[1]])-1
N_stock=10
stox.price<-matrix(nrow = N_days,ncol = N_stock)
stox.tag<-vector(length =N_stock)


for (i in 1:N_stock) {
  row<-strsplit(inp[i+1],"\\s+",perl = TRUE)[[1]]
  
  stox.price[,i]<-t(t(as.numeric(row[2:length(row)])))
  stox.tag[i]<-row[1]
  
}

stox.df<-data.frame(stox.price)
names(stox.df)<-stox.tag
rownames(stox.df) = 1:nrow(stox.df)

stox.df.logd<-log(stox.df)

stox.df.logd<-log(stox.df[2:N_days,]) - log(stox.df[1:N_days-1,])

Stox plots

par(mfrow=c(1,1))

for (name in names(stox.df)) {
  
  plot(as.matrix(stox.df[name]), main=name, type='b')
  
}

Stox plots log

par(mfrow=c(1,1))

for (name in names(stox.df)) {
  
  plot(as.matrix(stox.df.logd[name]), main=name, type='b')
  
}

### Calculate covariance matrix

stox.ret<-t(as.matrix(stox.df.logd))%*%matrix(data =1/(N_days-1), ncol=1, nrow=N_days-1)

target.ret = mean(stox.ret)

stox.df.logd.demeaned<-(stox.df.logd - matrix(data=1,nrow=N_days-1,ncol=1)%*%t(stox.ret))

stox.cov<-as.matrix(t(stox.df.logd.demeaned))%*%as.matrix(stox.df.logd.demeaned)/(N_days-2)

stox.std<-sqrt(diag(stox.cov))

stox.corr<-diag(stox.std^-1)%*%stox.cov%*%diag(stox.std^-1)

Calculate optimal portfolio
